\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. S. bavarica} Martinovský & H. Scholz,{\i  Willdenowia}{\b  4}: 322 (1968). Stems up to 70 cm. Leaves 1-1·3 mm in diameter, the basal softly hairy, at least in part, on the abaxial surface and with short hairs on the ribs on the adaxial surface, the upper leaves strongly scabrid; sheaths of the basal leaves with short, soft, dense hairs, the upper sparsely hairy on the back. Panicle contracted. Glumes long-attenuate. Lemma (21-)23-26 mm, the ventral line of hairs reaching the base of the awn; awn (31-)33-41(-45) cm, the column glabrous, the seta with hairs 3-4 mm. •{\i  S. Germany }({\i near Neuburg}). Ge.
