\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. S. endotricha} Martinovský, {\i Preslia}{\b  44}: 12 (1972). Stems shortly hairy below the nodes and throughout the uppermost internodes. Leaves with the abaxial surface glabrous and smooth. Lemma 18-21·5 mm; awn 24·5-27(-30) cm, the column glabrous, the seta plumose. •{\i  C. & S. Greece.} Gr.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. S. cretacea} P. Smirnov,{\i  Bull. Soc. Nat. Moscou} ser. 2, {\b 49}({\b 1}): 90 (1940). Leaves often flat when fresh, the abaxial surface smooth; sheaths of upper leaves puberulent and ciliate. Lemma 20-23 mm; awn (27-)30-33(-38) cm, the column glabrous, the seta plumose. •{\i  S.E. Russia} ({\i by the R. Don,} 90{\i  km N.W. of Volgograd}). Rs (E).
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. S. syreistschikovii} P. Smirnov,{\i  Del. Sem. Hort. Bot. Univ. Mosq.}{\b  1948}, 36 (1948). Leaves glabrous, tuberculate and scabrid on the abaxial surface and with short hairs only on the sides of the ribs on the adaxial surface; ligule of basal leaves 0·5-1 mm. Lemma (18-)20-21·5 mm; awn (32-)34-36(-37·5) cm, the column with hairs up to 2 mm and the seta with hairs 4(-6) mm.{\i  S.E. Krym.} Rs (K). ({\i Caucasus}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. S. iberica} Martinovský,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  73}: 150 (1966). Leaves strongly scabrid and aculeolate on the abaxial surface and shortly hairy, at least on the marginal ribs, on the adaxial surface; sheaths of basal leaves glabrous, of the upper ciliate and shortly hairy on the back. Glumes aristate. Lemma 18·5-21(-24) mm; awn c. 30 cm, the column between the geniculations with short, subappressed setae or only tuberculate and with scattered long, soft hairs. •{\i  S. France, C. & E. Spain.} Ga Hs.
